title: Command LIVE Spratly Spat-SKIDROW
description:
The People's Republic of China's primary foreign policy concerns are
energy security and trade. Its industrial might and economic strength
continues to multiply requiring significant resources from around the
world. The sea lines of communication (SLOC) between China and the
Middle East and Africa are the most vital and China has invested
heavily in expanding and modernizing its Navy to protect this route
denying potential adversaries the ability to influence Chinese policy
by cutting these vital lines and rolling back adversaries away from
the Chinese mainland
